Ternary operator:

· Ternary operator is a shorthand notation for if-else condition.

· It can be shorthand notation for nested if-else condition.
Syntax:

Condition? If true: if false

The first operand in ternary operator should be a Boolean. If the first operand is true then ternary operator returns second operand else it returns third operand.

Example:

int a = 10;

int b =20;

int result = a<b ? a : b;